	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.35]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>bwahahaha&nbsp;&nbsp; the way to Sebilis is a closely gaurded secret by a select few!   (j/k  ;)<br><br>preparations (after zoning into TT):<br><br>1.  Fresh sow<br>2.  Fresh UV (if you're night blind)<br>3.  Load Bind Affinity<br>4.  Invis up  (keep invis and Bind loaded)<br><br>When you zone into TT (from EJ), turn left and follow the wall untill till you can't go any further because of a gate.   Go right thru the gate, then to your left is another.  Go thru that as well.  Turn right, and follow the zone wall until you come to a camp.  Pass the camp a ways, then look off to your left and you will see some ruins in the not too far distance.  There is an archway type entry (to the right of a fallen pillar) that is sometimes guarded by spectral callers.  Wait until ghosts have wandered away (if you get aggro'd by anything, DO NOT train them to the Sebilis portal...this is a bind point for many and you often see naked players here.  They don't need to be dead again!!)  go thru the archway straight thru to the end (it isn't far), then turn left and go straight until you see a hole (ramp) in the floor.  Drop down and follow the tunnel until you come to the red and black orb.  Bind yourself near the orb so you don't have to make this run again.   Pick your Seb key up on your cursor (you do have your Seb key, right??), click on the orb...LOADING, PLEASE WAIT....  welcome to Old Sebilis!<br><br>Make a hotkey    /ooc lvl 53 shaman LFG<br><br>Note:  you can end up waiting a long time for a group in Seb, but it is more often than not worth the wait.<br><br>BTW...I wouldn't recommend going to Seb until you have reached lvl 51 (when you get Superior Healing).  Good Luck!!<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>Oracle of Novus Invictus<br>(Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>51 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
