	   <tr><td colspan=2>Since 2h blunt will give you the most damage during melee, i suggest putting some training points into it.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am playing a lvl13 shaman, and i noticed my 2h skills builds ever so slowly.  It was very frustrating, especially when I was trying to kill my first rabid grizzly!  Got killed, became bear's dinner.  So i went to halas and put about 20points into training and went from 12 to 55.  Wow, i was glad i did, cause from that point on, i was invincible and i died at most once per lvl since lvl 11.  I am almost lvl14 now, and looking back, it was the best training i could spend on.  By the way, when you are low lvl, you just want to get to lvl20 as fast as you can.  Your weapon skill decides very much if you could lvl smoothly.  Most people will tell you to save training points till later.  Why?  Because they would tell you to save them for trading skills, which will be very expensive.  On the other hand, if you got to high lvl earlier, faster.  That few hundred pps will come just with a snap of the finger.  So put some points to weapon skill and lvl fast with minimum deaths.  enjoy!  Oh, i forgot, you are lvl5, more the reason to max it out.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
