	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hail Shamans,<br><br>Im Zkorsyx DeathWind,Scaled Mystic of Cabilis.<br>Let me begin with saying Shamans kick ass. They are a variety class. In groups I buff,slow,haste,debuff,DoT,and nuke. We are wanted in groups because of our amazing ability to perform lots of roles that other classes cant. If you have noticed Druids,Shamans,Bards are the most powerful because of there variety. Movin away from that I need to say that the debate on Totemic/Northman should be viewed in all aspects. AC and Resists are imporant. You guys jabber on and on about shamans can melee/cast/heal! Take a look at the totemic armor. Verant designed it to fit a class that can do everything. Take a look at the AC(better tanking ability).Helm has 5WIS and AC. BP has lots of AC and resists, and so on. Northman is good for Barbarians because of the diety requirment. On the other hand im a Iksar Shaman, So I go with Scaled Mystic. Not many pieces have WIS on it but a well - balanced stat array. Resists/Mana/Wis/Melee stats. Armor depnds on race/diety/ability to wear armor. Also on the 1hb Issue/2hb/Piercering. 1hb is good because you can use a shield ex:CGS!2hb is good also though but you restrict WIS which is very important. At 50+ as a shaman you will never find yourself meleeing at all period. Leave that to the people who were deisgned to be tanks/damage dealers. <br><br>A Shamans Wisdom can not be compared~<br>Zkorsyx DeathWind<br>Scaled Mystic of Cabilis<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
